column11: What rating will you primarily be working on during the Winter term (January - April)?
column12: Are you scheduling Rotor-Wing or Fixed-Wing aircraft?

column20: I have submitted availability at Line Service to work morning shifts throughout this quarter/until I can apply at LEFA as an instructor, so I have blocked off weekday mornings to prevent scheduling conflicts with work. My wife has weekends off from her job so I prefer to keep the recurring schedule free on the weekends, and schedule weekend events on a case-by-case basis with my instructor.
Sat/Sun are the only days my wife has off. My cat prefers to hang out on weekends as well. 5am and 6am blocks too early for day flight. LEFA prohibits most maneuvers to be practiced at night.
